Indigestion:

• Indigestion refers to an upset stomach
• It is also referred to as dyspepsia

Symptoms to look for:

• Belching
• Nausea
• Bloated stomach
• Abdominal discomfort in upper abdominal area

Causes:

• Gastritis or GERD
• Symptom of peptic ulcer
• In some cases, it's a symptom of cancer
• Incorrect eating habits like:
   o Excessive intake of spicy or oily food
   o Overeating
   o Eating quickly
• Excessive consumption of coffee or alcohol
• Certain antibiotics
• Excessive smoking
• Anxiety

